																		placeholder
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/placeholder-mcd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6536693); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6536693&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610175952" alt="Placeholder McD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6536693)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/placeholder-mcd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6536693); return false;" >Placeholder McD</a></span> <span class="odate time_1604671717 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Nov 2020 14:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4812416">
									

<p>This is my love letter to 001 proposals, and my critique of the significance we put on them as a community. Yes, it has elements of many other proposals in it; this is by design. Each of these iterations includes concepts and tropes of proposals that I admire, with my own spin put on them.</p>
<p>As for what is literally happening here, I feel that all of the puzzle pieces are laid out, and anyone who is interested can discover a valid interpretation if they dig in enough. That being said, the precise details and mechanics of the anomaly/Jones construct and how it comes to be are not essential to the narrative and its intended meaning.</p>
<p>Thank you very much to everyone who gave critique on this. There were so many critters it's hard to remember them all, but each of them significantly contributed to my process of writing this.</p>
<p>Special thanks to HarryBlank and Yossi, who stuck with me through much of the process and reread the thing many times.</p>

							</div>

								
